    • Constructor Detail

      • Camera

        public Camera(Point3D position,
      Rotation rotation,
      float yFOV,
      float aspRatio,
      float zNear,
      float zFar)
        Parameters:
        position - Point3D representing the camera's position.
        rotation - Rotation representing the rotation of the camera.
        yFOV - The field of view angle, in degrees, in the y-direction. (copied from OpenGL docs)
        aspRatio - The aspect ratio that determines the field of view in the x-direction. The aspect ratio is the ratio of x (width) to y (height). (copied from OpenGL docs)
        zNear - The distance from the viewer to the near clipping plane (always positive). (copied from OpenGL docs)
        zFar - The distance from the viewer to the far clipping plane (always positive). (copied from OpenGL docs)

    • Method Detail

      • initPerspective

        public void initPerspective()
        Initializes the perspective. Essentially just sets up field of view, aspect ratio, and render distance.

      • doTranslations

        public void doTranslations()
        Translates the objects to account for camera position and rotation. This is because this code moves the camera in terms of the world, but OpenGL needs to have world coordinates relative to the camera.

      • doKeyboardControl

        public void doKeyboardControl()
        Handles keyboard movement. Controls are standard awsd/arrow keys with space bar to ascend and shift to descend.

      • doMouseControl

        public void doMouseControl()
        Handles changing pitch, yaw, and roll based on mouse control. Move the mouse to affect pitch and yaw, and use the mousewheel to change roll.
